sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Platform Operator
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Operator as KubeRay Operator<br/>(controller-runtime)
    participant HeadPod as Ray Head Pod<br/>8265/TCP HTTP
    participant WorkerPod as Ray Worker Pod
    participant KRBProxy as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Gateway as data-science-gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant ExtUser as External User<br/>(Browser)
    participant Redis as External Redis<br/>6379/TCP

    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
        Note over User,HeadPod: Flow 1: RayCluster Lifecycle
        User->>K8sAPI: Create RayCluster CR<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
        K8sAPI-->>Operator: Watch event (new RayCluster)
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create head pod, worker pods,<br/>services, RBAC<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
        K8sAPI-->>HeadPod: Pod scheduled & started
        K8sAPI-->>WorkerPod: Pod scheduled & started
        WorkerPod->>HeadPod: Connect to GCS Server<br/>6379/TCP, mTLS (if enabled)
        Operator->>HeadPod: Poll dashboard status<br/>8265/TCP HTTP
    end

    rect rgb(255, 243, 224)
        Note over User,HeadPod: Flow 2: RayJob Submission (K8sJobMode)
        User->>K8sAPI: Create RayJob CR<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
        K8sAPI-->>Operator: Watch event (new RayJob)
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create RayCluster (if needed)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create K8s Job (submitter)<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
        Note over Operator,HeadPod: Submitter Job Pod
        Operator->>HeadPod: ray job submit<br/>8265/TCP HTTP
        loop Poll job status
            Operator->>HeadPod: GET /api/jobs/{id}<br/>8265/TCP HTTP
            HeadPod-->>Operator: Job status response
        end
    end

    rect rgb(232, 245, 233)
        Note over ExtUser,HeadPod: Flow 3: Authenticated Dashboard Access (OIDC via Gateway API)
        ExtUser->>Gateway: HTTPS request to dashboard<br/>443/TCP TLS
        Gateway->>KRBProxy: Forward to head pod sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS
        KRBProxy->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount token
        K8sAPI-->>KRBProxy: Allowed / Denied
        alt Authorized
            KRBProxy->>HeadPod: Proxy to dashboard<br/>8265/TCP HTTP (localhost)
            HeadPod-->>KRBProxy: Dashboard response
            KRBProxy-->>Gateway: Response
            Gateway-->>ExtUser: Dashboard page
        else Denied
            KRBProxy-->>Gateway: 403 Forbidden
            Gateway-->>ExtUser: Access Denied
        end
    end

    rect rgb(252, 228, 236)
        Note over HeadPod,Redis: Optional: GCS Fault Tolerance
        HeadPod->>Redis: GCS data persistence<br/>6379/TCP, password auth (optional)
        Redis-->>HeadPod: Acknowledgment
    end
